#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.72"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.72:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.72:0.2"
msgid "7. Arahantavagga"
msgstr "7. The Perfected Ones"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.72:0.3"
msgid "72. Surādhasutta"
msgstr "72. With Surādha"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.81"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.72:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn22.72:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā surādho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Surādha said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn22.72:1.3"
msgid ""
"“kathaṃ nu kho, bhante, jānato kathaṃ passato imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye "
"bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānāpagataṃ mānasaṃ hoti, vidhā "
"samatikkantaṃ santaṃ suvimuttan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, how does one know and see so that the mind is rid of ego, "
"possessiveness, and conceit for this conscious body and all external stimuli;"
" and going beyond discrimination, it’s peaceful and well freed?”"

msgctxt "sn22.72:1.4"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ kiñci, surādha, rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ … pe … yaṃ dūre santike "
"vā, sabbaṃ rūpaṃ: ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā anupādāvimutto hoti."
msgstr ""
"“Surādha, one is freed by not grasping having truly seen any kind of form at "
"all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior "
"or superior; far or near: <em>all</em> form—with right understanding: ‘This "
"is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "sn22.72:1.5"
msgid "Yā kāci vedanā …"
msgstr "One is freed by not grasping having truly seen any kind of feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.72:1.6"
msgid "yā kāci saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.72:1.7"
msgid "ye keci saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.72:1.8"
msgid ""
"yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ "
"vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbā vedanā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse "
"or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: <em>all</em> consciousness—with "
"right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

# Handling of abbreviations here is corrupted. Not in PTS ed; this is found only in burmese edition.
msgctxt "sn22.72:1.9"
msgid "sabbā saññā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.72:1.10"
msgid "sabbe saṅkhārā …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.72:1.11"
msgid ""
"sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ: ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ "
"yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya disvā anupādāvimutto hoti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.72:1.12"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, surādha, jānato evaṃ passato imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye, bahiddhā "
"ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānāpagataṃ mānasaṃ hoti vidhā "
"samatikkantaṃ santaṃ suvimuttan”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"That’s how to know and see so that the mind is rid of ego, possessiveness, "
"and conceit for this conscious body and all external stimuli; and going "
"beyond discrimination, it’s peaceful and well freed.” …"

msgctxt "sn22.72:1.13"
msgid "aññataro ca panāyasmā surādho arahataṃ ahosīti."
msgstr "And Venerable Surādha became one of the perfected."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.72:1.14"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.72:1.15"
msgid "Arahantavaggo dutiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
